Description: Next-generation KDE fan control for Linux desktops
 KDE Fan Control is a next-generation fan control experience for the KDE
 desktop. A privileged Rust daemon owns hardware writes, applies per-fan
 PID policies, and exposes one DBus control surface to the GUI, tray, and
 CLI.
 .
 Features include:
  - Per-fan PID control with configurable gains, limits, and cadence
  - Multi-sensor aggregation (avg, max, min, median) so one fan can track
    the hottest component or the average across a thermal zone
  - Automatic hardware discovery from Linux hwmon sysfs
  - KDE-native GUI with overview, inventory, fan detail pages, and wizard setup
  - System tray integration with status notifications
  - Draft, validate, and apply lifecycle for reviewable configuration changes
  - Auto-tune proposals with explicit acceptance
  - Polkit-authenticated write operations with read-open DBus access
  - Fail-safe fallback and degraded-fan recovery